                                <div class="breast-text">
                                    <p>
                                        Labiaplasty is surgical reduction of the labia minora or inner skin that covers the clitoris
                                        and vaginal opening. This can be performed for both cosmetic and reconstructive reasons. Our 
                                        plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery (TOPS) perform Labiaplasty under local anesthetic 
                                        or general anesthetic depending on the patient’s comfort. During your consultation, your TOPS 
                                        plastic surgeon will discuss your goals as far as the functional improvements and appearance 
                                        you are looking for. From there, your plastic surgeon will determine if you are a candidate 
                                        for what is termed a “wedge resection” Labiaplasty which results in a more natural appearing 
                                        labia minora or a “trim” Labiaplasty, which results in a cleaner, but more dramatic change in 
                                        appearance. Your plastic surgeon will also determine if you require clitoral hood reduction, 
                                        which may improve stimulation during intercourse.
                                    </p>
