                                    Be prepared for your initial consultation to last 1 hour or more. New patient forms for patients desiring 
                                    Labiaplasty will have very personal questions about sexual satisfaction, urinary continence, and other 
                                    genitourinary symptoms that can be uncomfortable or embarrassing. While you may think many symptoms you 
                                    experience are embarrassing, many women deal with the same issues, and the physicians at The Oaks Plastic 
                                    Surgery are committed to helping you in the best way they can. After having a thorough discussion about 
                                    your concerns and goals, your TOPS plastic surgeon will perform a focused exam, which may require an 
                                    internal vaginal exam as well. Photographs and measurements will be taken for operative planning. After, 
                                    a detailed discussion about surgical or nonsurgical options will be discussed with you to meet your goals.
                                </span>
                            </p>
