                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can I expect the day of my Labiaplasty procedure in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p>If Labiaplasty is planned under local anesthesia, you will arrive at The Oaks Plastic Surgery Clinic and be brought into our procedure room. A strong topical anesthetic will be placed to the area to decrease or eliminate any pain you may have during the local anesthetic injection. You will be given a medication to help you relax during the procedure. Your plastic surgeon will then make very precise markings for operative planning. Local anesthetic will then be injected, and the procedure will begin once you are completely numb in the area. The procedure typically takes about 1 hour. Depending on which local anesthetic is injected, the surgical area will remain numb between 8 and 72 hrs. Antibiotic ointment will be placed on the incision lines and you will be sent home with disposable underwear and pads for the first several days. You will also be sent home with an anesthetic spray to help with the discomfort after your Labiaplasty procedure.</p>
                                <p>If Labiaplasty is planned under general anesthesia, your plastic surgeon will meet you in the preoperative care area the day of your Labiaplasty procedure. Extensive preoperative checks will be performed and you will get to meet the anesthesiologist and plastic surgery operative team. The procedure typically takes about 1 hour.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 " id="expect-recovery">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can I expect for my recovery from a Labiaplasty?</h3>
                                <p>Recovery from Labiaplasty is very similar to recovery from childbirth or an episiotomy. It is important to keep the area clean to prevent infection or wound healing complications. You will be given an antibiotic ointment to place on the area. You can expect some spotting after the procedure and should wear a liner or pad until this subsides. You can begin taking sitz baths after 36 hours, which may help ease some of the discomfort, but be very careful with the water temperature. Some patients choose to use numbing spray for the first two days to also help with any discomfort. Any pain should be greatly improved after the first week. We ask that you refrain from strenuous exercise for 2 weeks and intercourse for 6 weeks to allow for proper healing. The labia typically heal very well and scarring is almost completely unnoticeable.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
